54D1ir_6GN-JQarzsAONJZ0g5uyscvQ70H_N7PcdpAHvOpqSgSL0Q9yTaLnOQkw_OJoL5NC8uVThEs9Dc5fPBbE3NEbt2mSCAcpWOpXPkeFJg6hSWFVCCsNe5c98R4wfgmGGSIIt7NIUfN8gLfdp2k3n2rmbxFlmME0ZEaBiMxaGqSos7hiJ8HUSmVgKz4=\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL is a pure Java expression/reflection library and its only runtime dependency, Javassist, is already transitive from ognl:ognl:3.3.5, so no extra Maven dependency or Docker image is needed. However upstream OGNL 3.3.5 configures Java 9+ test runs with module opens, so meaningful reflective coverage may need JVM args beyond the normal scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"When generating tests that exercise OGNL reflective access against JDK classes, configure the test JVM with `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`. Do not enable or depend on installing a Java SecurityManager on JDK 25; avoid tests that call `System.setSecurityManager`, and keep `ognl.security.manager` unset unless explicitly testing OGNL's disabled/force-disabled initialization behavior.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"JDK 25 permanently disables SecurityManager support, so older OGNL security-manager tests can fail independently of reachability metadata.\",\n    \"OGNL's expression compiler uses Javassist at runtime; it is present transitively, but native-image validation remains authoritative for whether compiled-expression paths are usable.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b486e0b0a194a41016a4271ad46e4819791a340082e83513b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2825, "output": 1326, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30775, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782739357578, "responseId": "resp_0b486e0b0a194a41016a42719e